Cross-lingual Learning ofNamedEntities
Abstract:
Over the last decade, the phenomenal success of NLP
systems has been driven mainly by deep neural networks
labeled data. However, annotating data under all possible
real-world scenarios is often infeasible. As a result, these
systems may fail dramatically in practice when dealing with
data written in different languages. In this talk, I will present
works that are important to extend the generalization ability
of NLP systems across languages. In particular, we will focus
on understanding named entities (e.g., location, person) that
usually convey key information in a sentence. I will first
point out the translation artifacts of named entities in cross-
